# CODEOWNERS — file-ownership matrix from docs/AGENT_PLAN.md §4.
#
# GitHub requires CODEOWNERS entries to reference accounts with write
# access. The agent roles ("researcher", "tester", "developer",
# "reviewer", "auditor") are not GitHub identities — they are subagent
# roles defined in .claude/agents/*.md. Until those map to dedicated
# GitHub bot accounts, the orchestrator (@milmazz) is listed as the
# required reviewer and the role is recorded inline as a comment.
#
# When a role acquires its own GitHub identity, replace the @milmazz
# token on the relevant lines with that identity (and keep the role
# comment for humans).

# spec/ — Researcher (RW); Tester/Developer/Orchestrator read-only.
spec/                              @milmazz  # role: researcher
priv/repo/conformance_fixtures.sql @milmazz  # role: tester (Postgres fixtures)

# test/ — Tester (RW); Developer/Orchestrator read-only.
test/                              @milmazz  # role: tester
test/support/                      @milmazz  # role: tester

# lib/ — Developer (RW); Tester/Orchestrator read-only.
lib/                               @milmazz  # role: developer

# Build configuration — shared between Tester (test-only deps) and
# Developer (runtime deps); Orchestrator arbitrates.
mix.exs                            @milmazz  # role: developer + tester (split: test-only vs runtime deps)
mix.lock                           @milmazz  # role: developer + tester

# Orchestrator-only.
docs/STATUS.md                     @milmazz  # role: orchestrator
docs/AGENT_PLAN.md                 @milmazz  # role: orchestrator
.github/                           @milmazz  # role: orchestrator (CI, CODEOWNERS, templates)
